fetch-crl
------------------------------------------
The fetch-crl utility will retrieve certificate revocation lists (CRLs) for a
set of installed trust anchors, based on crl_url files or IGTF-style info
files. It will install these for use with OpenSSL, NSS or third-party tools.

Runtime requirements:
  perl-5.32.1-2
  perl-libwww-perl-6.67-1
  perl_base-5.32.1-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygport-0.35.5-1
  make-4.4-1

Canonical website:
  https://wiki.nikhef.nl/grid/FetchCRL3

Canonical download:
  https://dist.eugridpma.info/distribution/util/fetch-crl3/fetch-crl-3.0.23.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fetch-crl-3.0.23-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fetch-crl-3.0.23-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fetch-crl-3.0.23-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fetch-crl-3.0.23-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(fetch-crl)
  /etc/fetch-crl.conf
  /usr/sbin/clean-crl
  /usr/sbin/fetch-crl
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/fetch-crl.README
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/NOTICE
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/README
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/fetch-crl-boot.init
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/fetch-crl-cron.cron
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/fetch-crl-cron.init
  /usr/share/doc/fetch-crl/fetch-crl.conf.example
  /usr/share/man/man8/clean-crl.8.gz
  /usr/share/man/man8/fetch-crl.8.gz

